Togo President Faure Gnassingbe wins fourth term, as rival cries foul             AFP  24th Feb 2020 08:20:42 GMT +0300 AFP  24th Feb 2020 08:20:42 GMT +0300 AFP   Last May, Gnassingbe oversaw an overhaul of the constitution that allowed him to run this year -- and potentially remain in office until 2030. [AFP]  Last May, Gnassingbe oversaw an overhaul of the constitution that allowed him to run this year -- and potentially remain in office until 2030. [AFP] Last May, Gnassingbe oversaw an overhaul of the constitution that allowed him to run this year -- and potentially remain in office until 2030. [AFP] Last May, Gnassingbe oversaw an overhaul of the constitution that allowed him to run this year -- and potentially remain in office until 2030. Togo President Faure Gnassingbe has won a fourth term in power, the national electoral commission declared on Monday, as his main rival accused authorities of fraud.         Gnassingbe has led the country of eight million people since taking over in 2005 following the death of his father. [AFP]  Gnassingbe has led the country of eight million people since taking over in 2005 following the death of his father. [AFP] Gnassingbe has led the country of eight million people since taking over in 2005 following the death of his father. [AFP] Gnassingbe has led the country of eight million people since taking over in 2005 following the death of his father. He promised to form his own "inclusive government in the coming days", accusing authorities of using ballot stuffing and fake polling stations to skew the results in the incumbent's favour. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » Subscribe Now »  Stability and security              Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegr